<div class="row rowForEditablePanels"><div class="rowInner">            <div class="panels" columns="4">                 <div class="col">    <div class="editable">        <div class="itemBody">    <h3>                    <p>50th Anniversary Virtual Issue</p>            </h3>    <p>For the latest <em>Social History of Medicine</em> Virtual Issue, marking the 50th Anniversary of the Society, the Co-Editors invited previous Chairs of the society to select articles and book reviews from the SHM Archive. These articles reflect some of the early aims and professional intersections of the society, but also chart the dramatic changes in historical practice between the 1980s and now.</p><p><a data-link-id="ef708f90-a012-4255-bfd4-b1281a66c345" href="https://academic.oup.com/shm/pages/chairs-choices-anniversary-vi">Explore the Virtual Issue in full</a>.</p></div>    </div></div>                             <div class="col">    <div class="editable">        <div class="itemBody">    <h3>                    <p>Past Virtual Issues</p>            </h3>    <p><em>Social History of Medicine</em>&nbsp;presents a selection of articles and reviews from the archive on different themes published by the journal.</p><p><a data-link-id="86ce1a2f-2e3b-4249-a07e-1a58ea2cc7bd" href="https://academic.oup.com/shm/pages/virtual_issue_archive">Browse the Virtual Issues archive</a>.</p></div>    </div></div>                             <div class="col">    <div class="editable">        <div class="itemBody">    <h3>                    <p>The Roy Porter Essay Prize</p>            </h3>    <p>The 2022 Roy Porter Student Essay Prize was awarded to Anna Weerasinghe (Johns Hopkins University) for her entry: '‘In the Kitchen with Brianda Jaoa: Tacit Practices and Technologies of Healing in Garcia de Orta’s Coloquios (1563)’.</p><p><a data-link-id="771844c6-0f05-4d4b-8966-a61ceee815ba" href="https://academic.oup.com/shm/pages/porter_prize">Find out more about the prize.</a></p></div>    </div></div>                             <div class="col">    <div class="editable">        <div class="itemBody">    <h3>                    <p>Open Access Articles</p>            </h3>    <p>A number of articles in <em>Social History of Medicine</em> have been published online as open access.</p><p><a data-link-id="3252c49f-1463-442c-91eb-bcc7991bab6f" href="https://academic.oup.com/shm/search-results?q=&amp;access_openaccess=true">Browse all</a></p></div>    </div></div>             </div></div></div>
    
